Saipem, Petroci Study Gas Terminal in Ivory Coast, Matin Says

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-10-19T10:26:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/saipem-petroci-study-gas-terminal-in-ivory-coast-matin-says.html
Petroci ,  Ivory Coast ’s state-owned
oil company, signed a deal with Saipem SpA of  Italy  to consider
developing a floating natural-gas storage terminal and a
pipeline in the east of the country, according to a statement
published in Fraternite Matin.  The companies will study the possibilities to meet “rising
domestic and regional demand for electricity,” according to the
statement printed in the Abidjan-based, state-owned  newspaper 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Abidjan via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 